    <h3>Architecture Highlights</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <h4>Modular Design</h4>
        <p>Each workflow module is self-contained with its own:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Domain Models (State enums, entities)</li>
            <li>Services (Data access, business rules, state machine management)</li>
            <li>Events (Domain events for state transitions)</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Type-Safe State Management</h4>
        <p>Enum-based states eliminate string parsing and provide compile-time safety:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>LodState / FormalLodState (state enums)</li>
            <li>LodTrigger / FormalLodTrigger (trigger enums)</li>
            <li>Direct enum comparisons throughout the codebase</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Async Event Handling</h4>
        <p>All state machine callbacks use async patterns:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>OnEntryAsync for state entry actions</li>
            <li>OnExitAsync for state exit actions</li>
            <li>Non-blocking notification service integration</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
